original_result.user_prompt: What's VT100 code to render green terminal text?
original_result.completion_text:
The VT100 is a computer terminal that uses ANSI escape codes to control its display functions. If you want to render green text on a terminal emulator supporting VT100, you can use the following ANSI escape sequence:


```
\033[32mThis text will be displayed in green.\033[0m
```

In this sequence, `\033` represents the ESC character, `[32m` specifies the green color attribute, `This text will be displayed in green.` is the text you wish to appear in green, and finally, `\033[0m` resets all attributes back to their defaults. This works well in modern terminal emulators that support ANSI escape codes.
